I've been thinking about a ton of stuff recently. I talked a lot with some of my family when they were over today. About my uncle's wedding, relationships of people in my family. It was weird/cool.

I never realized how much I am appreciated. That probably sounds terribly conceited but it made me really happy just to hear little things people had to say. I know I probably don't make half the people who I really appreciate feel appreciated. I'm bad at that.

Have you ever had one of those people in your life who you thought was the greatest person you could ever meet? Someone you loved, who you really looked up to. I don't know exactly what I'm getting at. I've lost a lot of respect for that person in my life recently. Not so much respect but I don't really look up to them anymore. I don't think people realize how much they affect other people, that or they don't care. I had a really hard time talking about this tonight, like on the verge of tears. I don't understand myself. This is stupid.

And you know your best friend? I don't know if I really have a best friend. Things are weird. I feel like I don't have that person to call at three in the morning just to talk to because it's been a bad week. There are tons of people who I would love to hear from at three in the morning. I wouldn't feel comfortable calling someone to tell them my problems. I don't doubt that there are a handful of people that I could call if I needed someone to talk to but I wouldn't. There's something wrong with me. Why am I even writing this? Seriously.

Today was pretty cool. I got to talk to some really great people.

Yesterday was a lot of fun. We should do that again sometime.

I'm hanging out with EVERYONE this summer. It will be the best.

It has been decided that I should shut up forever.

 

Kaley.

I was thinkging. Woudn't it be cool if it was summer forever? But it would only be cool for so long. The novelty would wear off. We wouldn't appreciate it as much as we do at the end of a long school year.

You know those people who you can just sit there and laugh with for hours about nothing? I love those people.

And those people who you can have the best serious conversation with.

What about those people who you never got a chance to know?

I've been thinking a lot recently about the people in your lives and how they got there. What if we met someone at a different time in our lives, or never at all. Why is it that we meet the people we meet? What if one of us never took the initiative? I was just thinking about how our lives could be so different based on who we are friends with. Your close group of friends, in a sense, represents all that you are. If that group was different, you would be different. Just something to think about, I guess.

Everything happens for a reason.

I hope that made atleast a little bit of  sense.

 

Kaley.

You know what I really don't like? When people think that they know and they don't. Does anybody really know all of the things that I am thinking? Does anybody really know what is good for me? I mean there are obvious physical needs that any person can point out. Nobody can tell me that they know or that they're only trying to help me because who would know what is better for me other than myself?

Why would someone tell me that nothing really matters now. It won't mean anything in 5 or 6 years. Yes it will. I will always have memories of today and this year. It doesn't make sense if only the future matters. The future isn't something that will come and be here because it's always the future. For someone to say that it would mean that nothing matters. Unless they mean the only thing that matters is when I die. It's hard for me to sit there and listen to this and not say something. If nothing now will matter in 5 or 6 years what will ever matter?

Don't pretend like you care or you want to talk to me if you don't because I don't want to talk to you either.

I think my head just might explode.

Kaley.

My mother tells me Karen called. Of course I wasn't home. Man, I miss her. I wish I was there to catch the call.

I really need summer to get here. I can't wait. I want to go to The Lake a lot more this year. Even though we went a lot last year. This year will be more fun.

I don't know exactly what happened and I'm not exactly investigating...but really if you were in her situation would you want the whole school talking about you? Regardless of your opinion or whatever. Just stop.
Why? I feel like everyone is setting me up for a big let down. Maybe I'm right..maybe they are...

It wasn't a bad monday, but it wasn't a good monday. haha I was in an extremely weird mood today..I guess since I say that oh so often that would mean that I'm always in a weird mood.
